This paper is about knowledge-grounded dialogue, which involves natural language processing and machine learning. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with the intersection of computer science and linguistics. Other relevant sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
